list.name: Test Start
list.query: SELECT first(*) FROM "$task"..testStartEnd WHERE type='started' and "nodeName"='$testName'

list.name: Test End
list.query: SELECT last(*) FROM "$task"..testStartEnd WHERE type='finished'  and "nodeName"='$testName'

description: This dashboard shows live load test metrics provided by JMeter.

panels.content: The following panels show aggregated metrics for all requests

targets.query: SELECT last("startedThreads") FROM "$task".."virtualUsers" WHERE $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName'
SELECT 1 - sum("errorCount")/count("responseTime") FROM "$task".."requestsRaw" WHERE $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName'
SELECT  count("responseTime") FROM "$task".."requestsRaw" WHERE $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName'
SELECT sum("errorCount")/count("responseTime") FROM "$task".."requestsRaw" WHERE $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName'
SELECT last("finishedThreads") FROM "$task".."virtualUsers" WHERE $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName'
SELECT  count("responseTime")/$aggregation FROM "$task".."requestsRaw" WHERE $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName'  GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT mean("startedThreads") FROM "$task".."virtualUsers" WHERE $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName'  GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT  count("responseTime")/$aggregation FROM "$task".."requestsRaw" WHERE $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName' GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(linear)
SELECT mean("startedThreads") FROM "$task".."virtualUsers" WHERE $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName'  GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT mean(responseTime) FROM "$task".."requestsRaw"  WHERE $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName' GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(linear)

SELECT count(responseTime) as Count, mean(responseTime) as Avg, min(responseTime) as Min, max(responseTime) as Max, median(responseTime) as Median, percentile(responseTime, 75) as "75%", percentile(responseTime, 90) as "90%",percentile(responseTime, 95) as "95%",percentile(responseTime, 99) as "99%",  (sum(errorCount)/count(responseTime)) as "Error Rate" FROM "$task".."requestsRaw"  WHERE $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName' and requestName=~/.* transaction/ GROUP BY requestName

panels.content: The following panels show request-specific metrics for the request "[[request]]"

targets.query: SELECT count("responseTime")/$aggregation FROM "$task".."requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName'  GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(linear)
SELECT 1 - sum("errorCount")/count("responseTime") FROM "$task".."requestsRaw" WHERE $timeFilter AND "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ and "nodeName" = '$testName'
SELECT count("responseTime") FROM "$task".."requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName'
SELECT sum("errorCount")/count("responseTime") FROM "$task".."requestsRaw" WHERE $timeFilter AND "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ and "nodeName" = '$testName'
SELECT min("responseTime")  FROM "$task".."requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName'  GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT max("responseTime") FROM "$task".."requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName'  GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT percentile("responseTime", 90) FROM "$task".."requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName'  GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT percentile("responseTime", 95) FROM "$task".."requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName'  GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT percentile("responseTime", 99) FROM "$task".."requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName'  GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
SELECT sum("errorCount")/$aggregation FROM "$task".."requestsRaw" WHERE "requestName" =~ /^$request$/ AND $timeFilter and "nodeName" = '$testName'  GROUP BY time([[aggregation]]s) fill(null)
